### Question 13
A circle has a circumference of \(89\pi\) centimeters. What is the diameter, in centimeters, of the circle?

questions.question_text: A circle has a circumference of \(89\pi\) centimeters. What is the diameter, in centimeters, of the circle?
questions.explanation: The circumference formula is C = πd, so d = C/π = 89π/π = 89 centimeters.
